import os
import cv2
def random_rotating(img):
    rot_img=np.rot90(img,np.random.randint(1,4))
    return rot_img
def vertical_flipping(image):
    ver_flip=image[-1::-1,::]
    return ver_flip
def Horizontal_flipping(image):
    hor_flip=image[:,::-1]
    return hor_flip
def translation_along_x(src_img,x_distance):
    h,w = src_img.shape[:2]
    ts_mat = np.array([[1,0,x_distance],[0,1,0]])
    out_img = np.zeros(src_img.shape,dtype='u1')
    for i in range(h):
        for j in range(w):
            origin_x = j
            origin_y = i
            origin_xy = np.array([origin_x,origin_y,1])
            
            new_xy = np.dot(ts_mat,origin_xy)
            new_x = new_xy[0]
            new_y = new_xy[1]

            if 0<new_x < w and 0<new_y < h:
                out_img[new_y,new_x]  = src_img[i,j]
    return out_img
def translation_along_y(src_img,y_distance):
    h,w = src_img.shape[:2]
    ts_mat = np.array([[1,0,0],[0,1,y_distance]])
    out_img = np.zeros(src_img.shape,dtype='u1')
    
    for i in range(h):
        for j in range(w):
            origin_x = j
            origin_y = i
            origin_xy = np.array([origin_x,origin_y,1])
            
            new_xy = np.dot(ts_mat,origin_xy)
            new_x = new_xy[0]
            new_y = new_xy[1]

            if 0<new_x < w and 0<new_y < h:
                out_img[new_y,new_x]  = src_img[i,j]
    return out_img
def cropping(image, crop_size):
    h, w,  = image.shape[:2]
    top = np.random.randint(0, h - crop_size[0])
    left = np.random.randint(0, w - crop_size[1])
    bottom = top + crop_size[0]
    right = left + crop_size[1]
    image_crop = image[top:bottom, left:right, :]
    return image_crop
def zooming(img_in,x,y,width,height):
    array = np.array(img_in)
    Zom_array= array[y:y + height,x:x+width] 
    return Zom_array
def color_modification(image,n):
    imag_col = np.array(image)
    imag_col[imag_col[:, :, 2] < 255, 2] = n
    return imag_col
def light_gaussian_noise(img,par):
    img=img[...,::-1]/255.0
    noise =np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=1, size=img.shape)
    noisy = np.clip((img + noise*par),0,1)
    return noisy
def light_gaussian_noise1(img_in):
        array = (np.array(img_in))/255
        row,col,ch= array.shape 
        mean=0
        var=0.5
        sigma=np.sqrt(var)
        noise=np.random.normal(mean,sigma,(row,col,ch))
        im_gauss=array+noise
        return im_gauss
#Without cv2
def adding_illumination1(img_in):
    array = np.array(img_in)
    A = 1.1 #alpha
    B = 75   #beta
    add_illu_im = np.zeros(array.shape,array.dtype)
    for x in range(array.shape[0]):
          for y in range(array.shape[1]):
                for z in range(array.shape[2]):
                      add_illu_im[x,y,z] = np.clip(A*array[x,y,z] + B, 0, 255)  
    return add_illu_im
#Using cv2
def adding_illumination(image, gamma=4.0):
    invGamma= 1.0 / gamma
    table = np.array([((i / 255.0) ** invGamma) * 255 for i in np.arange(0, 256)]).astype("uint8")
    return cv2.LUT(image, table)

#dogs
directory="C:/Users/21656/Desktop/dogs" #Folder that contains 5 normal images of dogs
directory_save="C:/Users/21656/Desktop/Train/Dogs/"#Folder that contains the augmented images that we will use later as the training data in the binary classfication
directory_save_test="C:/Users/21656/Desktop/Test/Dogs/"#Folder that contains the augmented images that we will use later as the Validation data in the binary classfication
#Acces the folder (dogs) and iterate over with original images and apply the transformations on evey 
#image and save 70% of the augmented images as training data and 30% as Testing data
def application_transformation(directory,directory_save,directory_save_test):
    i=0
    for filename in os.listdir(directory):
        i+=1
        image = Image.open(directory+"/"+filename)
        image=image.resize((300,300))
        image.save(directory_save+filename)
        im=np.array(Image.open(directory+"/"+filename), dtype=np.uint8)
        Image.fromarray(random_rotating(im)).save(directory_save+"Image_rotation"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG')
        Image.fromarray(cropping(im, [70,70])).save(directory_save+"Image_crop"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG')
        Image.fromarray(translation_along_x(im,50)).save(directory_save+"Image_translation_along_x"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG')
        Image.fromarray(translation_along_y(im,50)).save(directory_save+"Image_translation_along_y"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG') 
        Image.fromarray((light_gaussian_noise(im,0.2)* 255).astype(np.uint8)).save(directory_save+"Image_noise"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG') 
        Image.fromarray(zooming(im,100,100,70,70)).save(directory_save+"Image_zoom"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG') 
        Image.fromarray(color_modification(im,np.random.randint(1,255))).save(directory_save+"Image_colorm"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG') 
        Image.fromarray(Horizontal_flipping(im)).save(directory_save_test+"Image_fliph"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG')
        Image.fromarray(vertical_flipping(im)).save(directory_save_test+"Image_flipv"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG')
        Image.fromarray(adding_illumination(im)).save(directory_save_test+"Image_illumination"+str(i)+".jpg",'JPEG')
        
application_transformation(directory,directory_save,directory_save_test)

def Visualize(im,im1):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2)
    ax[0][0].imshow(im)
    ax[0][1].imshow(im1)
    ax[1][0].hist(im.ravel(),256,[0,256])
    ax[1][1].hist(im1.ravel(),256,[0,256])
    ax[0][0].set_ylabel('Original Image')
    ax[0][1].set_ylabel('Augmented Image')
    colors = ("red", "green", "blue")
    plt.figure()
    plt.xlim([0, 256])
    for channel_id, color in enumerate(colors):
        histogram, bin_edges = np.histogram(
            im1[:, :, channel_id], bins=256, range=(0, 256)
        )
        plt.plot(bin_edges[0:-1], histogram, color=color)
    plt.title("Color Histogram of the augmented image")
    plt.xlabel("Color value")
    plt.ylabel("Pixel count")
